snippet: Lindsey Vonn of the U.S., stricken with flu-like symptoms, finished fourth in a World Cup downhill race Saturday. Elisabeth Görgl of Austria was the winner.
abstract: Elisabeth Gorgl of Austria ends Lindsey Vonn’s four-race unbeaten streak in speed events by winning a World Cup downhill race in Bad Kleinkirchheim, Austria.
lead_paragraph: Lindsey Vonn of the U.S., stricken with flu-like symptoms, finished fourth in a World Cup downhill race Saturday. Elisabeth Görgl of Austria was the winner.

headline.seo: Skiing — Ailing Vonn Is Fourth as Streak Ends in Speed Events
headline.main: Streak Ends as Vonn Is Fourth in Downhill
